abel="Rate this recipe 5 out of 5 stars" onmouseenter="window.WPRecipeMaker.userRating.enter(this)" onfocus="window.WPRecipeMaker.userRating.enter(this)" onmouseleave="window.WPRecipeMaker.userRating.leave(this)" onblur="window.WPRecipeMaker.userRating.leave(this)" onclick="window.WPRecipeMaker.userRating.click(this, event)" onkeypress="window.WPRecipeMaker.userRating.click(this, event)" style="font-size: 1em;"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" x="0px" y="0px" width="16px" height="16px" viewbox="0 0 24 24"><g  transform="translate(0, 0)"><polygon fill="none" stroke="var(--wp--custom--color--star)" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="square" stroke-miterlimit="10" points="12,2.6 15,9 21.4,9 16.7,13.9 18.6,21.4 12,17.6 5.4,21.4 7.3,13.9 2.6,9 9,9 " stroke-linejoin="miter"/></g></svg></span><div class="wprm-recipe-rating-details wprm-block-text-normal">No ratings yet</div></div></div></div><div class="post-header__meta"><div class="post-header__author"><a href="https://www.dinneratthezoo.com/about-me-contact-info/" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1" class="entry-avatar"><img alt='' src='https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/008b9a079f72a6cc33350130cf7f24feb9662a4ff3c0b86432495a1547c4addf?s=36&#038;d=mm&#038;r=g' srcset='https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/008b9a079f72a6cc33350130cf7f24feb9662a4ff3c0b86432495a1547c4addf?s=72&#038;d=mm&#038;r=g 2x' class='avatar avatar-36 photo' height='36' width='36' decoding='async'/></a> <a href="https://www.dinneratthezoo.com/about-me-contact-info/" class="entry-author">Sara Welch</a></div><p class="post-header__date"><span>Published:</span> Feb 09, 2026</p></div></div></div></div><div class="site-inner" id="main-content"><div class="content-area"><main class="site-main" role="main"><article class="type-post grow-content-body"><div class="entry-content">
<p>These <strong>pink cupcakes</strong> are light and fluffy pink velvet cake topped with a swirl of homemade cream cheese frosting and sprinkles. An <em>easy and elegant dessert</em> that&rsquo;s perfect for parties!</p>



<p>When I&rsquo;m looking to impress, I turn to dessert recipes like <a href="https://www.dinneratthezoo.com/black-forest-cupcakes/">black forest cupcakes</a>, <a href="https://www.dinneratthezoo.com/nutella-cake/">Nutella cake</a>, <a href="https://www.dinneratthezoo.com/red-velvet-brownies/">red velvet brownies</a> and these beautiful pink velvet cupcakes.</p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img fetchpriority="high" decoding="async" width="1200" height="1800" data-pin-description="These pink cupcakes are light and fluffy pink velvet cake topped with a swirl of homemade cream cheese frosting and sprinkles. An easy and delicious dessert that's perfect for parties!" data-pin-title="Pink Cupcakes" src="https://www.dinneratthezoo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/pink-cupcakes-final-1.jpg" alt="Pink cupcakes topped with pink cream cheese frosting and pearl sprinkles." class="wp-image-48112" srcset="https://www.dinneratthezoo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/pink-cupcakes-final-1.jpg 1200w, https://www.dinneratthezoo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/pink-cupcakes-final-1-700x1050.jpg 700w, https://www.dinneratthezoo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/pink-cupcakes-final-1-768x1152.jpg 768w, https://www.dinneratthezoo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/pink-cupcakes-final-1-1024x1536.jpg 1024w, https://www.dinneratthezoo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/pink-cupcakes-final-1-400x600.jpg 400w, https://www.dinneratthezoo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/pink-cupcakes-final-1-276x414.jpg 276w, https://www.dinneratthezoo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/pink-cupcakes-final-1-128x192.jpg 128w, https://www.dinneratthezoo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/pink-cupcakes-final-1-378x567.jpg 378w" sizes="(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px" data-pin-media="https://www.dinneratthezoo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/pink-cupcakes-final-1.jpg"></figure>



<p>Sometimes you just need a fun burst of color to turn a regular cupcake into a fun and festive treat! These pink cupcakes are simple to make, full of flavor, and are great for Valentine&rsquo;s Day, gender reveal parties, bridal showers and so many other occasions.</p>


<div class="wp-block-yoast-seo-table-of-contents yoast-table-of-contents"><h2 id="table-of-contents">Table of Contents</h2><ul><li><a href="#h-pink-cupcakes-ingredients">Pink Cupcakes Ingredients</a></li><li><a href="#h-how-do-you-make-pink-cupcakes">How Do You Make Pink Cupcakes?</a></li><li><a href="#h-tips-for-the-perfect-cupcakes">Tips For The Perfect Cupcakes</a></li><li><a href="#h-quick-tip">Quick Tip</a></li><li><a href="#h-recipe-faqs">Recipe FAQs</a></li><li><a href="#h-flavor-variations">Flavor Variations</a></li><li><a href="#h-more-dessert-recipes">More Dessert Recipes</a></li><li><a href="#h-love-this-recipe">Love This Recipe?</a></li><li><a href="#wprm-recipe-container-48107">Pink Cupcakes Recipe</a></li></ul></div>


<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="h-pink-cupcakes-ingredients">Pink Cupcakes Ingredients</h2>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img decoding="async" width="1200" height="1800" data-pin-description="These pink cupcakes are light and fluffy pink velvet cake topped with a swirl of homemade cream cheese frosting and sprinkles. An easy and delicious dessert that's perfect for parties!" data-pin-title="Pink Cupcakes" src="https://www.dinneratthezoo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/pink-cupcakes-ingredients.jpg" alt="Ingredients including butter, sugar, flour, egg, cream cheese and pink food coloring." class="wp-image-48114" srcset="https://www.dinneratthezoo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/pink-cupcakes-ingredients.jpg 1200w, https://www.dinneratthezoo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/pink-cupcakes-ingredients-700x1050.jpg 700w, https://www.dinneratthezoo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/pink-cupcakes-ingredients-768x1152.jpg 768w, https://www.dinneratthezoo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/pink-cupcakes-ingredients-1024x1536.jpg 1024w, https://www.dinneratthezoo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/pink-cupcakes-ingredients-400x600.jpg 400w, https://www.dinneratthezoo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/pink-cupcakes-ingredients-276x414.jpg 276w, https://www.dinneratthezoo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/pink-cupcakes-ingredients-128x192.jpg 128w, https://www.dinneratthezoo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/pink-cupcakes-ingredients-378x567.jpg 378w" sizes="(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px" data-pin-media="https://www.dinneratthezoo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/pink-cupcakes-ingredients.jpg"></figure>



<p>To make this recipe, you will need all purpose flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt, granulated sugar, buttermilk, unsalted butter, vegetable oil, an egg, vanilla extract, white vinegar, pink gel food coloring, cream cheese, powdered sugar and pink sprinkles.</p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="h-how-do-you-make-pink-cupcakes">How Do You Make Pink Cupcakes?</h2>



<p>Start by preparing the pink velvet cake batter. Preheat the oven, and place some pink cupcake liners into muffin tins. Sift the dry ingredients into a large bowl, and stir to combine. Add the wet ingredients to a separate bowl, and whisk to blend. Mix the wet ingredients into the dry ingredients, then stir until you have a batter. Divide the batter among the cupcake liners, then bake. Cool the cupcakes completely on a wire rack.</p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img decoding="async" width="1200" height="1800" data-pin-description="These pink cupcakes are light and fluffy pink velvet cake topped with a swirl of homemade cream cheese frosting and sprinkles. An easy and delicious dessert that's perfect for parties!" data-pin-title="Pink Cupcakes" src="https://www.dinneratthezoo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/pink-cupcakes-process-collage-1.jpg" alt="Process shots showing how to make cupcake batter." class="wp-image-48116" srcset="https://www.dinneratthezoo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/pink-cupcakes-process-collage-1.jpg 1200w, https://www.dinneratthezoo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/pink-cupcakes-process-collage-1-700x1050.jpg 700w, https://www.dinneratthezoo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/pink-cupcakes-process-collage-1-768x1152.jpg 768w, https://www.dinneratthezoo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/pink-cupcakes-process-collage-1-1024x1536.jpg 1024w, https://www.dinneratthezoo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/pink-cupcakes-process-collage-1-400x600.jpg 400w, https://www.dinneratthezoo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/pink-cupcakes-process-collage-1-276x414.jpg 276w, https://www.dinneratthezoo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/pink-cupcakes-process-collage-1-128x192.jpg 128w, https://www.dinneratthezoo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/pink-cupcakes-process-collage-1-378x567.jpg 378w" sizes="(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px" data-pin-media="https://www.dinneratthezoo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/pink-cupcakes-process-collage-1.jpg"></figure>



<p>To make the frosting, beat the butter and vanilla extract together until they are light and fluffy. Add the powdered sugar, 1 cup at a time, and cream to combine. Beat the cream cheese in a separate bowl. Add the cream cheese to the butter and sugar, and mix until you have a smooth and creamy frosting. Add the pink food coloring, then the frosting is ready to use.</p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1200" height="1800" data-pin-description="These pink cupcakes are light and fluffy pink velvet cake topped with a swirl of homemade cream cheese frosting and sprinkles. An easy and delicious dessert that's perfect for parties!" data-pin-title="Pink Cupcakes" src="https://www.dinneratthezoo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/pink-cupcakes-process-collage-2.jpg" alt="Butter, cream cheese and powdered sugar in a mixing bowl to make frosting." class="wp-image-48117" srcset="https://www.dinneratthezoo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/pink-cupcakes-process-collage-2.jpg 1200w, https://www.dinneratthezoo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/pink-cupcakes-process-collage-2-700x1050.jpg 700w, https://www.dinneratthezoo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/pink-cupcakes-process-collage-2-768x1152.jpg 768w, https://www.dinneratthezoo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/pink-cupcakes-process-collage-2-1024x1536.jpg 1024w, https://www.dinneratthezoo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/pink-cupcakes-process-collage-2-400x600.jpg 400w, https://www.dinneratthezoo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/pink-cupcakes-process-collage-2-276x414.jpg 276w, https://www.dinneratthezoo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/pink-cupcakes-process-collage-2-128x192.jpg 128w, https://www.dinneratthezoo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/pink-cupcakes-process-collage-2-378x567.jpg 378w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px" data-pin-media="https://www.dinneratthezoo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/pink-cupcakes-process-collage-2.jpg"></figure>



<p>Place the frosting in a large piping bag fitted with a star tip. Pipe a peak of frosting onto a cupcake, then pipe around the peak three times to create the perfect swirl. Add a few sprinkles. Repeat the process with the rest of the cupcakes, then serve and enjoy!</p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1200" height="1800" data-pin-description="These pink cupcakes are light and fluffy pink velvet cake topped with a swirl of homemade cream cheese frosting and sprinkles. An easy and delicious dessert that's perfect for parties!" data-pin-title="Pink Cupcakes" src="https://www.dinneratthezoo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/pink-cupcakes-process-collage-3.jpg" alt="A piping bag adding frosting on top of pink cupcakes." class="wp-image-48118" srcset="https://www.dinneratthezoo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/pink-cupcakes-process-collage-3.jpg 1200w, https://www.dinneratthezoo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/pink-cupcakes-process-collage-3-700x1050.jpg 700w, https://www.dinneratthezoo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/pink-cupcakes-process-collage-3-768x1152.jpg 768w, https://www.dinneratthezoo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/pink-cupcakes-process-collage-3-1024x1536.jpg 1024w, https://www.dinneratthezoo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/pink-cupcakes-process-collage-3-400x600.jpg 400w, https://www.dinneratthezoo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/pink-cupcakes-process-collage-3-276x414.jpg 276w, https://www.dinneratthezoo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/pink-cupcakes-process-collage-3-128x192.jpg 128w, https://www.dinneratthezoo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/pink-cupcakes-process-collage-3-378x567.jpg 378w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px" data-pin-media="https://www.dinneratthezoo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/pink-cupcakes-process-collage-3.jpg"></figure>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="h-tips-for-the-perfect-cupcakes">Tips For The Perfect Cupcakes</h2>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li>The cupcakes can be stored in the refrigerator <em>for 3 days</em>. They are best enjoyed at room temperature so one to two hours before serving, remove from the refrigerator. The cupcakes can be stored un-frosted in a container in the freezer for up to 3 months.</li>



<li>You can add <strong>more food coloring</strong> for a more intense pink color. Use less food coloring for a paler hue.</li>



<li>Feel free to use any type of <em>pink sprinkles</em> that you like. I used pink pearls which I purchased at my local craft store.</li>



<li>If you don&rsquo;t have a piping bag, you can use an <strong>offset spatula </strong>to frost the cupcakes. You fill one corner of a resealable plastic bag with frosting, then snip the tip off.</li>
</ul>


<div class="block-tip cwp-inner has-background has-tertiary-background-color">

<h2 class="wp-block-heading has-text-align-center block-tip__title" id="h-quick-tip">Quick Tip</h2>



<p class="has-text-align-center">I recommend using a gel food coloring for the <em>best color</em>. You can purchase this type of food color online or in craft stores.</p>

</div>

<div class="block-faq-title cwp-inner has-background has-quaternary-background-color">

<h2 class="wp-block-heading has-text-align-center block-faq-title__title" id="h-recipe-faqs">Recipe FAQs</h2>



<div class="schema-faq wp-block-yoast-faq-block"><div class="schema-faq-section" id="faq-question-1709235805226"><strong class="schema-faq-question">Can I put sprinkles on cupcakes the day before?</strong> <p class="schema-faq-answer">You can put your sprinkles on cupcakes the day before you plan to serve them. I recommend adding the sprinkles as soon as you place the frosting on the cupcakes so that the sprinkles will stick before the frosting has time to harden.</p> </div> <div class="schema-faq-section" id="faq-question-1709238346152"><strong class="schema-faq-question">What is the secret to moist cupcakes?</strong> <p class="schema-faq-answer">To get the moist cake, I recommend adding some oil to your batter. Oil tends to add more moisture than butter. I typically use a combination of both oil and butter, for the perfect balance of moisture and rich flavor.</p> </div> </div>

</div>

